1. d4 Nf6 2. Nc3 d5 3. Bf4 c5 4. e3 {This is the soundest reply.} a6 5. dxc5 Qa5 
6. Nf3 Qxc5 7. Be2 {[%cal Be1g1] White first brings his King to safety before 
starting play on the Queenside.} Nc6 8. O-O Bf5 9. Na4 {[%cal 
Ba1c1,Bc2c4,Ga4c5,Ga4b6][%csl Rc5,Rb6] Starting to exploit Black's weakened 
Queenside dark squares.} Qa7 10. Rc1 {This is also good, intending c4 with an 
initiative.} b5 11. Nc3 {[%cal Gc3d5,Gd1d5,Gc3b5,Ge2b5][%csl Rd5,Rb5] White 
threatens to take on d5 and b5.} e6 12. Nxb5 {[%cal Be2b5,Bf3d4]} ({+- After} 
12. Nxb5 12... axb5 13. Bxb5 Qb7 14. Nd4 Rc8 15. c4 $1 {White will soon regain 
his sacrificed material with interest.}) *

