1. d4 Nf6 2. Nc3 d5 3. Bf4 c5 4. e3 {This is the soundest reply.} a6 5. dxc5 Nc6 
{This signals that Black wants to play ...e5.} 6. a3 {[%cal Bb2b4] We should 
take up the challenge and try to hold on to the c5-pawn.} e5 {[%csl Rf4]} 7. Bg5 
{[%cal Gg5d8,Gc3d5,Gd1d5][%csl Rd5,Rf6,Rd8] Threatening Bxf6 followed by Nxd5.} 
Be6 {[%cal Ge6d5]} 8. b4 {[%cal Bg1f3,Bf1e2,Be1g1][%csl Gc5,Gb4,Ga3] Thus we get 
to hold on to our extra pawn.} Be7 9. Nf3 O-O 10. Be2 h6 11. Bh4 {White is a 
pawn up and Black does not have sufficient compensation for this deficit.} *

