1. d4 Nf6 2. Nc3 d5 3. Bf4 c5 4. e3 {This is the soundest reply.} cxd4 5. exd4 
Bg4 {[%cal Gg4d1][%csl Rd1]} 6. f3 {[%cal Gf3g4][%csl Rg4] We usually chase the 
Bishop around if Black posts it aggressively.} Bf5 7. Nb5 {[%cal Gb5c7][%csl 
Rc7]} Na6 8. c3 {[%cal Gc3b4][%csl Gb4,Rf5,Ra6]} ({Making sure that Black has no 
tricks with ...Nb4. Black now has to make a tough choice, as} 8. c3 8... e6 
{would allow us to chase the Bishop around with} 9. g4 $1 Bg6 10. h4 {.}) *

