1. d4 Nf6 2. Nc3 d5 3. Bf4 c5 4. e3 {This is the soundest reply.} cxd4 5. exd4 
a6 6. Nf3 {Played by Rapport.} Bg4 7. h3 Bxf3 {This avoids the problems after 
...Bh5 g4, but gives up the Bishop pair.} 8. Qxf3 {Most players would prefer 
White though Black is solid.} Nc6 9. O-O-O {[%cal Bg2g4]} b5 10. g4 {[%cal 
Bg4g5,Bh3h5] Once again when White has castled Queenside it is imperative to 
understand that time is of the essence and the key expansion must take place on 
the Kingside without delay.} e6 11. g5 Ng8 12. h4 Bd6 13. Ne2 {[%cal 
Be2f4,Bf1h3]} Nge7 14. Bh3 Bxf4+ 15. Nxf4 Ng6 16. h5 Nxf4 17. Qxf4 {[%cal 
Bg5g6,Bh5h6] White has a clear edge due to his space advantage, lead in 
development and Bishop vs. Knight. I would be very happy if every opening 
brought me such an outcome.} *

