his structure, as we saw at the start of this course in the 'Common Ideas' 
section.} 5. Bd3 {[%cal Bg1f3]} Bxf4 6. exf4 {[%cal Gf4e5,Gd4e5][%csl 
Gd4,Gf4,Rc8] This transposes to variation #6.} *

