1. d4 d5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. Bf4 e6 4. e3 Bd6 {This is also an idea, but I am not sure 
Black ever wants to exchange on f4, as after exf4 White has actually improved 
his structure as we saw at the start of this course in the 'Common Ideas' 
section.} 5. Bd3 O-O 6. Nf3 {[%cal Gf3e5][%csl Ge5]} Bxf4 7. exf4 {[%cal 
Gf4e5,Gd4e5,Bf3e5,Bd1f3,Bf3h3][%csl Ge5,Rh7] White has great control of the 
centre and a good game. He can play Ne5, Qf3 and even Qh3 to start an attack.} *

[Event "The Jobava London System"]
[Site "Theory 4 (3... e6)"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
