1. d4 d5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. Bf4 e6 4. e3 Bb4 5. Bd3 c5 {[%cal Bc5c4,Bf6e4][%csl 
Rd3,Rc3] Other moves are less worrying as they would give White time to play 
Nge2 with a very comfortable position. 5... c5 is critical.} 6. dxc5 {Otherwise 
Black will play ...c4 followed by ...Ne4 with some advantage.} Nbd7 (6... Bxc3+ 
{is an option but it directly transposes into line #7.}) 7. Nge2 O-O 8. Bd6 
{[%csl Gd6,Gc5,Rf8]} Re8 9. Bb5 {[%cal Gb5e8][%csl Re8,Rd7] Preventing Black 
from immediately regaining his pawn.} Ne4 10. a3 {[%csl Rb4]} Bxc3+ 11. Nxc3 
Nxc3 12. bxc3 {[%cal Ba1b1,Be1g1] This would make it difficult for Black to win 
his pawn back.} *

