1. d4 d5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. Bf4 e6 4. e3 Bb4 5. Bd3 c5 {Other moves are less worrying 
as they would give White time to play Nge2 with a very comfortable position. 
5... c5 is critical.} 6. dxc5 Nbd7 7. Nge2 O-O 8. Bd6 Re8 9. Bb5 Ne4 10. a3 
Bxc3+ 11. Nxc3 Nxd6 12. cxd6 a6 13. Bxd7 Qxd7 14. Qd4 {[%cal Be1g1][%csl Gd4] 
Both sides are solid. I would very marginally pick White due to my preference 
for the Knight over the Bishop in a closed position. A sample line continues as 
follows:} Qxd6 15. O-O b6 16. e4 {[%cal Gd4d6][%csl Rd6,Gd4] Taking advantage of 
the fact that Black's Queen is undefended.} Bb7 17. exd5 ({and after} 17. exd5 
17... exd5 {the position is equal.}) *

