1. d4 d5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. Bf4 e6 4. e3 Bb4 5. Bd3 c5 {Other moves are less worrying 
as they would give White time to play Nge2 with a very comfortable position. 
5... c5 is critical.} 6. dxc5 Nbd7 7. Nge2 O-O 8. Bd6 Re8 9. Bb5 a6 {This puts 
