White first clarifies the situation on the Kingside.} fxg6 8. dxc5 {This move 
was the choice of Aronian on 2 occassions, both leading to online victories over 
Nepomniatchi.} Nc6 {[%cal Be7e5,Gc6e5][%csl Rf4]} 9. Nf3 {[%cal 
Gf3e5,Gf3d4][%csl Ge5,Gd4]} Qa5 {[%cal Ga5e1,Ga5c5]} 10. Qd2 {[%cal Gd2a5]} Qxc5 
{There are chances for both sides here. A sample line may be as follows:} 11. 
