1. d4 Nf6 2. Nc3 d5 3. Bf4 g6 4. e3 Bg7 5. h4 O-O 6. h5 {This is the most 
aggressive and best move after Black played 5... O-O. I think Black is inviting 
trouble. White has to be prepared to sacrifice an exchange, but it's well worth 
it.} Nxh5 {This is the type of position which a computer might be able to hold 
as Black but it requires very accurate defence which is well beyond the powers 
of most people.} 7. Rxh5 gxh5 8. Qxh5 {White's plan is not subtle but it doesn't 
need to be. It's a direct attack on Black's King. Currently Black only has his 
dark-squared Bishop defending the King. If he has any realistic chance of 
surviving he will need to bring in reinforcements and blunt White's threats.} f5 
9. Qh2 {[%cal Gh2c7][%csl Gf4,Gh2,Rc7] I think this is consistent and best.} Nd7 
10. Nxd5 {[%cal Gd5c7,Gh2c7][%csl Rc7]} *

