Ngf6 6. Qd4 {A common idea in these positions. The Queen is a good piece and 
White prepares to castle Queenside in some cases. White has the advantage, for 
example,} e5 {This is a rather desperate move, but with Bf4 and c6 coming Black 
had to do something.} 7. Qxe5+ {[%cal Gb5e8][%csl Rd7,Re8]} Be7 8. Be3 {[%cal 
Ge3c5][%csl Gc5] Bringing the bits out. White doesn't need to do anything 
heroic.} O-O {[%csl Re5]} 9. Bxd7 {Simplifying into a good position.} Nxd7 10. 
Qg3 Nxc5 {Black has won a pawn back, but at what cost?} 11. Rd1 Qa5 12. Nge2 
{[%cal Be1g1,Bc3d5,Be3d4,Gd4g7,Gg3g7][%csl Rg7] White has great piece 
development. He will castle and play Nd5 and Bd4 with an attack against Black's 
King.} *

