following response.} 6. Bb5+ {This is a very annoying check for Black to cope 
with.} Bd7 7. dxe6 fxe6 8. Qe2 {[%cal Gc3e4,Ge2e4,Bg1h3,Bh3g5,Gg5e4,Gg5e6][%csl 
Re4] White is doing well and will more likely than not win a pawn back at some 
point.} Nc6 {[%cal Bc6d4]} 9. Bxc6 {Exchanging the Knight before Black is able 
to play ...Nd4.} Bxc6 10. Nh3 {[%cal Bh3g5,Gg5e6,Gg5e4] With Ng5 on its way. 
White will soon regain the pawn.} *

