[Comment "the-jobava-london-system/course/28333, variation/4883086"]

1. d4 d5 2. Nc3 c5 {A logical enough move, but one that is not so popular at the 
higher levels. I believe the reason for this is that it allows White the option 
of sacrificing a pawn and this way go into an Albin Countergambit, but with an 
