Against 2 Nc3 it is still a popular choice. Here we should continue with the 
standard plan against ...Bf5 which is f3 followed by g4.} 3. f3 Bg6 {Stepping 
out of the way of e4 and g4.} 4. e4 dxe4 5. fxe4 Nf6 6. Bd3 Nc6 {[%cal 
Gc6d4,Gd8d4][%csl Rd4]} 7. Nf3 {[%cal Gf3d4]} e6 8. a3 {[%cal Ga3b4][%csl 
Gb4,Gd4,Ge4] White prevents Bb4. The central pawns give White an edge. Note that 
the d-pawn is poisoned.} Nxd4 9. Nxd4 Qxd4 10. Bb5+ {[%cal Bd1d4][%csl Rd4,Re8] 
Winning the Queen on d4.} *

