concerned about how to meet this move and other lines with ...Bb4. This is 
understandable. Black pins the c3-Knight and has various options, including 
taking on c3 and ...Nd5 or ...Ne4. White should respect this line, but I also 
feel that by being prepared and understanding the position it should not be 
feared.} 4. e3 {This is the choice of Jobava.} Nd5 {This move can look dangerous 
for White and avoids transpositions into lines already covered by not playing 
4... d5.} 5. Nge2 {This is a necessary reply. I am going to focus on what looks 
to be Black's best option which is when he captures the Bishop on f4.} Nxf4 6. 
